<TITLE> BCL men attack BNP offices in Barisal </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Barisal, Aug 5 (bdnews24.com)Bangladesh Chhatra League of BM College in Barisal attacked the BNP district and metropolitan offices Tuesday night in protest at an attack on a BCL leader, witnesses said. They said Jatiyatabadi Chhatra Dal leader Firoz Khan Kalu allegedly demanded money from BCL leader of BM College 'BDR Sohel' on Tuesday. As Sohel refused the extortion money Kalu along with seven to eight people went to the campus and beat up Sohel. He was rushed to sadar hospital immediately and brought back to Muslim Hall after treatment. Additional police were deployed on Sadar Road and around the campus after the incident as tension ran high. BCL adherents demonstrated on the campus protesting the attack and informed the Kotwali police of the matter. Later, they attacked the BNP offices. Kalu alleged that BCL activists damaged his College Road house and rooms of JCD leaders and activists of Sergeant Fazlul Haque Hall. BM College principal Nani Gopal Das said a criminal named 'Kalu' attacked students. The general students demanded his punishment, he added. Kotwali Model Police Station chief Md Nuruzzaman Chowdhury said that they had not received any written complaint yet but were trying to detain the perpetrators. He said neither Kalu's home nor any BNP office was damaged and added that some students hurled stones at the BNP office. Barisal district BNP joint convener Nazrul Islam Khan said they would call an emergency meeting and launch a movement. 
